data.title: Pub Conan Doyle
data.meta_description:
Arthur Doyle, the author and creator of Sherlock Holmes, was born in Edinburgh in 1859. His parents were immigrants from Ireland. The Conan Doyle Pub and a statue of Sherlock Holmes is located near Doyle's birthplace.
	
	Conan Doyle Pub: 71-73 York Place, Edinburgh
